# PIC16F877A 7-Segment Display Counter

This project demonstrates how to interface a **single 7-segment display** with the **PIC16F877A** microcontroller using **PORTC**. The program displays digits from **0 to 9**, changing every second.

## Features

- Displays digits **0–9** sequentially.
- 1-second delay between each digit.
- Uses a lookup table for segment patterns.
- Written in Embedded C using the **MPLAB XC8 Compiler**.

## Hardware Requirements

- PIC16F877A Microcontroller
- Common Anode 7-Segment Display
- Current-limiting resistors (220Ω–330Ω)
- 20 MHz Crystal Oscillator
- Two 22 pF Capacitors
- 5V Power Supply
- Breadboard and Connecting Wires

## Pin Connections

| 7-Segment Pin | PIC16F877A |
|---------------|------------|
| a–g, dp       | PORTC (RC0–RC7) |

> **Note:** The segment values in the program are for a **Common Anode** 7-segment display.

